      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DUST ASIDE (3) led last start and got the job done in impressive fashion, running away to score by 6.4L. He was dominant there and the inside draw can see him adopt similar tactics today. Has confidence now and can go on with the job. MAJESTUOSO PHOENIX (1) is ready to break through after collecting his 4th minor placing in a row last time over 1000m at this track after being in contention all the way. Likely improver with strong prospects. DEMETRIOUS (6) has not won for a long while. Last raced on June 28 when sixth at this track over 1435m. Suitably placed so anticipating a better run this time. WHAT'S THE POINT (4) finished eighth over 1695m at Bunbury at his most recent appearance on September 29. Lines up today for the first time for trainer Robert Gulberti. Has found a suitable race and is worth including. OLE GRANDE (7) is better than he showed last start and can put his best foot forward.",
